<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf66c2f1c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3709"><num value="3709">§ 3709.</num><heading> Exemptions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may exempt a vessel from the minimum requirements established by sections 3704–3706 of this title for segregated ballast, crude oil washing, and dedicated clean ballast if the Secretary decides that shore-based reception facilities are a preferred method of handling ballast and that adequate facilities are readily available.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf66c2f1d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/524">97 Stat. 524</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
